{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9edff399-4d37-4e39-91fe-747b5826da41","content":"This is a TUnit project which uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) natively. TUnit uses `--treenode-filter` with a path-like syntax (`/Assembly/Namespace/Class/Test`):\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"\n```\n\nThis matches all tests inside the `SmsNotificationTests` class regardless of assembly or namespace.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"90bf51c9-7dc6-4ae4-9528-76233d5bdd82","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"This is a TUnit project. TUnit uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) by default. For MTP-based runners, the filter syntax is different from VSTest.\n\nFor TUnit with MTP, you use `--treenode-filter` to filter tests. To filter by class name:\n\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"\n```\n\nThe treenode filter pattern for TUnit is: `/Assembly/Namespace/Class/Test`\n\nSo to match the class `SmsNotificationTests`:\n\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*/*/SmsNotificationTests/*\"\n\n\n```\n\nLet me verify this is correct for TUnit 0.6.120 with MTP. The treenode filter uses a path-like structure where wildcards match each level of the test hierarchy. The command I have should work to filter tests by class name.\n\nCompleting the filter...\n\n```","outputTokens":426,"requestId":"340F:222DF7:A9709D:C7C5EE:69F40287"},"id":"676e6ad6-8a02-4d4c-9ba8-27ceae0581de","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:32:01.337Z","parentId":"ef41452a-9e11-42c8-8e24-18832a595d08"}
